{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":879,"text":"Joseph Keller used to jog\naround the Stanford campus,"},{"time":4975,"text":"and he was struck by all the women\njogging there as well."},{"time":9716,"text":"Why did their ponytails swing\nfrom side to side like that?"},{"time":13867,"text":"Being a mathematician,\nhe set out to understand why."}]},{"cues":[{"time":17029,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":18204,"text":"Professor Keller was curious\nabout many things:"},{"time":20534,"text":"why teapots dribble"},{"time":22525,"text":"or how earthworms wriggle."},{"time":24847,"text":"Until a few months ago,\nI hadn't heard of Joseph Keller."},{"time":28581,"text":"I read about him in the New York Times,"},{"time":31457,"text":"in the obituaries."},{"time":32913,"text":"The Times had half a page\nof editorial dedicated to him,"},{"time":36709,"text":"which you can imagine is premium space\nfor a newspaper of their stature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":41368,"text":"I read the obituaries almost every day."},{"time":44690,"text":"My wife understandably thinks\nI'm rather morbid"},{"time":47736,"text":"to begin my day with scrambled eggs\nand a \"Let's see who died today.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":52160,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":54025,"text":"But if you think about it,"},{"time":55341,"text":"the front page of the newspaper\nis usually bad news,"},{"time":58778,"text":"and cues man's failures."},{"time":60777,"text":"An instance where bad news\ncues accomplishment"},{"time":63467,"text":"is at the end of the paper,\nin the obituaries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":67405,"text":"In my day job,"},{"time":68793,"text":"I run a company that focuses\non future insights"},{"time":71293,"text":"that marketers can derive\nfrom past data --"},{"time":73737,"text":"a kind of rearview-mirror analysis."},{"time":77092,"text":"And we began to think:"},{"time":78271,"text":"What if we held a rearview mirror\nto obituaries from the New York Times?"},{"time":84514,"text":"Were there lessons on how you could get\nyour obituary featured --"},{"time":88006,"text":"even if you aren't around to enjoy it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":90007,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":91515,"text":"Would this go better with scrambled eggs?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":94167,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":96163,"text":"And so, we looked at the data."},{"time":99869,"text":"2,000 editorial, non-paid obituaries"},{"time":104387,"text":"over a 20-month period\nbetween 2015 and 2016."},{"time":108053,"text":"What did these 2,000 deaths --\nrather, lives -- teach us?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":112901,"text":"Well, first we looked at words."},{"time":114958,"text":"This here is an obituary headline."},{"time":116743,"text":"This one is of the amazing Lee Kuan Yew."},{"time":119063,"text":"If you remove the beginning and the end,"},{"time":121609,"text":"you're left with a beautifully\nworded descriptor"},{"time":124967,"text":"that tries to, in just a few words,\ncapture an achievement or a lifetime."},{"time":129666,"text":"Just looking at these is fascinating."},{"time":132301,"text":"Here are a few famous ones,\npeople who died in the last two years."},{"time":135620,"text":"Try and guess who they are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":136963,"text":"[An Artist who Defied Genre]"},{"time":138427,"text":"That's Prince."}]},{"cues":[{"time":140497,"text":"[Titan of Boxing and the 20th Century]"},{"time":142358,"text":"Oh, yes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":143542,"text":"[Muhammad Ali]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":144790,"text":"[Groundbreaking Architect]"},{"time":146360,"text":"Zaha Hadid."}]},{"cues":[{"time":148843,"text":"So we took these descriptors"},{"time":150615,"text":"and did what's called\nnatural language processing,"},{"time":153163,"text":"where you feed these into a program,"},{"time":154958,"text":"it throws out the superfluous words --"},{"time":156847,"text":"\"the,\" \"and,\" -- the kind of words\nyou can mime easily in \"Charades,\" --"},{"time":161094,"text":"and leaves you with the most\nsignificant words."},{"time":163311,"text":"And we did it not just for these four,"},{"time":165156,"text":"but for all 2,000 descriptors."},{"time":167699,"text":"And this is what it looks like."},{"time":171004,"text":"Film, theatre, music, dance\nand of course, art, are huge."},{"time":176485,"text":"Over 40 percent."},{"time":178455,"text":"You have to wonder\nwhy in so many societies"},{"time":181007,"text":"we insist that our kids pursue\nengineering or medicine or business or law"},{"time":185466,"text":"to be construed as successful."},{"time":187871,"text":"And while we're talking profession,"},{"time":189588,"text":"let's look at age --"},{"time":190763,"text":"the average age at which\nthey achieved things."},{"time":193297,"text":"That number is 37."},{"time":196274,"text":"What that means is,\nyou've got to wait 37 years ..."},{"time":199954,"text":"before your first significant achievement\nthat you're remembered for --"},{"time":203373,"text":"on average --"},{"time":204548,"text":"44 years later, when you\ndie at the age of 81 --"},{"time":207050,"text":"on average."}]},{"cues":[{"time":208242,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":209267,"text":"Talk about having to be patient."}]},{"cues":[{"time":210975,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":212056,"text":"Of course, it varies by profession."},{"time":214566,"text":"If you're a sports star,"},{"time":215783,"text":"you'll probably hit\nyour stride in your 20s."},{"time":217934,"text":"And if you're in your 40s like me,"},{"time":220603,"text":"you can join the fun world of politics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":222618,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":223698,"text":"Politicians do their first and sometimes\nonly commendable act in their mid-40s."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227637,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":228918,"text":"If you're wondering what \"others\" are,"},{"time":230879,"text":"here are some examples."},{"time":232821,"text":"Isn't it fascinating, the things people do"},{"time":234961,"text":"and the things they're remembered for?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":236867,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":240136,"text":"Our curiosity was in overdrive,"},{"time":242004,"text":"and we desired to analyze\nmore than just a descriptor."},{"time":246998,"text":"So, we ingested the entire\nfirst paragraph of all 2,000 obituaries,"},{"time":251968,"text":"but we did this separately\nfor two groups of people:"},{"time":254766,"text":"people that are famous\nand people that are not famous."},{"time":257567,"text":"Famous people -- Prince,\nAli, Zaha Hadid --"},{"time":260280,"text":"people who are not famous\nare people like Jocelyn Cooper,"},{"time":264539,"text":"Reverend Curry"},{"time":265717,"text":"or Lorna Kelly."},{"time":266910,"text":"I'm willing to bet you haven't heard\nof most of their names."},{"time":270122,"text":"Amazing people, fantastic achievements,\nbut they're not famous."},{"time":274720,"text":"So what if we analyze\nthese two groups separately --"},{"time":277532,"text":"the famous and the non-famous?"},{"time":279081,"text":"What might that tell us?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":280524,"text":"Take a look."},{"time":284556,"text":"Two things leap out at me."},{"time":286569,"text":"First:"},{"time":288106,"text":"\"John.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":289328,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":291914,"text":"Anyone here named John\nshould thank your parents --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":295326,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":296679,"text":"and remind your kids to cut out\nyour obituary when you're gone."},{"time":301061,"text":"And second:"},{"time":303849,"text":"\"help.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":306524,"text":"We uncovered, many lessons\nfrom lives well-led,"},{"time":310013,"text":"and what those people immortalized\nin print could teach us."},{"time":312873,"text":"The exercise was a fascinating testament\nto the kaleidoscope that is life,"},{"time":317635,"text":"and even more fascinating"},{"time":320374,"text":"was the fact that the overwhelming\nmajority of obituaries"},{"time":323466,"text":"featured people famous and non-famous,"},{"time":326488,"text":"who did seemingly extraordinary things."},{"time":329574,"text":"They made a positive dent\nin the fabric of life."},{"time":332708,"text":"They helped."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334772,"text":"So ask yourselves as you go\nback to your daily lives:"},{"time":337387,"text":"How am I using my talents to help society?"},{"time":340331,"text":"Because the most powerful lesson here is,"},{"time":343328,"text":"if more people lived their lives\ntrying to be famous in death,"},{"time":347688,"text":"the world would be a much better place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":351062,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":352255,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}